# Project Structure Templates

**Purpose:** Standard project structure templates for different project types.

**When to use:** When starting a new project or organizing existing code.

**Related:**
- Python: `.cursor/agents/python-developer/AGENTS.md`
- C++: `.cursor/agents/cpp-developer/AGENTS.md`

## Python Project

```
project/
├── src/
│   └── module_name/
│       ├── __init__.py
│       ├── main.py
│       └── utils.py
├── tests/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── test_module_name.py
│   ├── test_integration.py
│   └── fixtures/
│       └── test_data.json
├── pyproject.toml
├── .ruff.toml
├── mypy.ini
├── .pre-commit-config.yaml
└── README.md
```

## C++ Project

```
project/
├── include/
│   └── project/
│       └── module.h
├── src/
│   └── module.cpp
├── tests/
│   └── test_module.cpp
├── CMakeLists.txt
└── README.md
```

## ROS Project

```
ros_package/
├── CMakeLists.txt
├── package.xml
├── msg/
│   └── CustomMessage.msg
├── srv/
│   └── CustomService.srv
├── src/
│   └── node_name.cpp
├── scripts/
│   └── node_name.py
├── launch/
│   └── node_name.launch
└── test/
    └── test_node.cpp
```

## Mixed Python/C++ Project

```
project/
├── include/
│   └── project/
│       └── cpp_module.h
├── src/
│   ├── cpp_module.cpp
│   └── python_module/
│       ├── __init__.py
│       └── main.py
├── tests/
│   ├── test_cpp_module.cpp
│   └── test_python_module.py
├── CMakeLists.txt
└── pyproject.toml
```

## General Principles

1. **Separate source and tests** - Keep test code separate from production code
2. **Organize by feature** - Group related files together
3. **Use clear naming** - Follow naming conventions (snake_case for files/dirs)
4. **Include configuration files** - Place config files at project root
5. **Document structure** - Include README.md explaining project layout
